headline: Travelers Sees $1.7 Billion Pretax Catastrophe Losses From California Wildfires
summary: The devastating wildfires that struck southern California in January could cost the insurance industry overall about $30 billion, according to analyst estimates.

headline: Travelers Announces Preliminary Catastrophe Loss Estimate for January 2025 California Wildfires
summary: NEW YORK, February 11, 2025--The Travelers Companies, Inc. (NYSE: TRV) today announced a preliminary estimate of catastrophe losses related to the January 2025 California wildfires.

headline: Travelers expects $1.7 billion insured loss from the California wildfires. Analysts still expect a profit.
